        "translation": "<p><strong>Part C Longer Conversations</strong></p><p><strong>Directions:</strong> In Part C, you will hear two longer conversations. The conversations will be read twice. After you hear each conversation , you are required to fulfill in the numbered blanks with the information you have heard. Write your answers on your answer sheet.</p><p><strong>Blanks 17 through 20 are based on the following coaversation.</strong><br/></p><p>W: Good morning, sir. May I help you?</p><p>M: It&#39;s our anniversary today. I&#39;m looking for the same flowers as the ones at her wedding banquet.</p><p>W: What do they look like?</p><p>M: White. They are white.</p><p>W: How tall are they?</p><p>M: They&#39;re short,I guess,about the same height as those short flowers over there.</p><p>W: So they look like roses?</p><p>M: No, they look like little bells.</p><p>W: Oh... lilies of the valley. No, I&#39;m sorry. We&#39;re out of them at the moment.</p><p>M: Oh,that&#39;s too bad.</p><p>W: What about roses?</p><p>M: OK. How many do you suggest?</p><p>W: As many as you like,sir. They&#39;re beautiful,aren&#39;t they?</p><p>M: Yes, they are.</p><p><strong>Blanks 21 through 24 are based on the following conversation.</strong></p><p>W: Were you caught in the thunderstorm yesterday?</p><p>M: Yes. The rain came all of a sudden and I got as wet as a drovraed rat.</p><p>W: Luckily I was not out at that time, but I was no less scared at the thunder and lightning.&nbsp;</p><p>M: It could be dangerous to walk in the thunderstorm, especially in the countryside.</p><p>W: Yes. The morning paper says that a young man got electric shock while running in the rain yesterday.</p><p>M: Really? Was the man killed?</p><p>W: The paper says he&#39;s still in hospital. I do hope he will survive.</p><p>M: The weather is really terrible this summer.</p><p>W: That&#39;s true. This is the hottest summer in thirty years. I wonder how long the hot wave will last.</p><p>M: I&#39;m afraid the terrible weather will not be gone till the end of September.</p><p>W: Have you noticed that summer is getting longer and longer in recent years?</p><p>M: Exactly. Our globe is getting warmer each year, especially in big cities like Shanghai.</p><p>W: I do wish the cool weather could come soon.</p>",
